{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7dbc7070-ae55-4d15-bb19-d890c61c257c","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you direct guidance instead.\n\nHere are the main tools for analyzing `.dmp` files from .NET apps:\n\n**1. `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, easiest)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n```\nUseful commands inside the session:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**2. `lldb` with SOS** (Linux)\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core <your-file.dmp>\n```\n\n**3. WinDbg / Visual Studio** (Windows)\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file? If so, provide the path to the `.dmp` file and I'll walk through the investigation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5c378a71-77dd-4c44-b4d3-09c17a932ac9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description specifically says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should not invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":363,"requestId":"418D:3F6047:62AD0DF:6BF55D8:69F164C0"},"id":"da3beadc-b78d-4567-b68b-6eb6175fc153","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:54:19.284Z","parentId":"18241bba-16a3-48d7-9b43-1e446b117d3f"}
